### Current Listings by County

The following table provides an approximate count of the current listings within each county. These figures are derived from the National Register Information Database as of April 24, 2008, and subsequent weekly updates. It's crucial to note that these numbers are dynamic, with additions and occasional removals occurring regularly. Therefore, these counts serve as a general indication rather than an official, definitive tally. Furthermore, the numbers presented here exclude modifications to existing listings, such as boundary increases or decreases, which are assigned separate reference numbers. For precise figures, one should consult the individual county list-articles.

Notable examples that grace these listings include the [Phil Hoffman House](/Phil_Hoffman_House) in Mahaska County, the serpentine [Snake Alley](/Snake_Alley_(Burlington,_Iowa)) in Des Moines County, and the [Lock and Dam No. 14 Historic District](/Lock_and_Dam_No._14_Historic_District) in Scott County. The striking [Grotto of the Redemption](/Grotto_of_the_Redemption) in Palo Alto County and the architecturally significant [Merchants' National Bank](/Merchants%27_National_Bank) in Poweshiek County, designed by the renowned Louis Sullivan, are also highlighted. Other notable sites include the [Howes Building](/Howes_Building) in Clinton County and the [Fourth Street Historic District](/Fourth_Street_Historic_District_(Sioux_City,_Iowa)) in Woodbury County.

